title: Hotel Mumbai
subTitle: A hotel staff risks everything to keep its patrons safe during a terror attack, especially a British heiress, her husband and her infant.

title: Chakravyuh
subTitle: Kabir infiltrates a Maoist organisation to help Adil Khan, who is a decorated police officer and his friend. As he gets deeper into the organisation, Kabir starts sympathising with the group's plight and starts having second thoughts.

title: Sniff
subTitle: Sunny, who lacks the sense of smell, finds his olfactory abilities enhanced after becoming a victim of a laboratory accident, which turns him into a superhero.

title: Sonchiriya
subTitle: After their leader's death, a group of dacoits splits up and runs away. On the way, they meet two women and help them escape their family and reach the hospital.

title: Iqbal
subTitle: Iqbal, a speech and hearing impaired boy, wishes to play cricket for the Indian team but his impairment overshadows his talent. Thus, he seeks help from a former cricket player to train him.

title: Thappad
subTitle: Amrita, a young woman, leads a content life with her husband, Vikram. However, their happiness is shattered when he slaps her at an office party, causing her to file for a divorce.

title: Tarla
subTitle: With dreams bigger than every social barrier known to women, Tarla Dalal embarks on an inspirational journey to change the country's culinary landscape.

title: Rustom
subTitle: Rustom, a naval officer, shares a happy relationship with his wife Cynthia. Soon, he discovers her affair with Vikram, a close friend, and is accused of murdering him.

title: Tumbbad
subTitle: Vinayak Rao, a resident of the village Tumbbad, repeatedly steals the ill-fated wealth of the evil Hastar, until his greed and heinous acts become the reason for his doom.

title: Mr. & Mrs. Mahi
subTitle: Former cricketer Mahendra marries Mahima, a doctor with a passion for cricket. However, upon discovering her exceptional skills, he encourages her to pursue a professional career in the sport.

title: Sharmaji Namkeen
subTitle: After a widower is forced into early retirement, he sets out to find another occupation to overcome his boredom. He meets a widowed boutique owner, and the two start to form a relationship.

title: English Vinglish
subTitle: A housewife and caterer, Shashi, is usually mocked by her family for not knowing English. Her attempt to learn the language helps her rediscover herself and reassert her value as a mother and a wife.

subTitle: Silsila works as a loyal subordinate to a don, but complications arise when he unwittingly becomes a pawn in his boss's evil plan.

title: Jail

title: Lost

title: India Lockdown
subTitle: The lives of four individuals - a father, his pilot daughter, a prostitute, and a migrant worker - are thrown into turmoil when the Indian government announces a nationwide lockdown.

title: Kanjoos Makkichoos
subTitle: Jamnaprasad Pandey intends to send his parents on a pilgrimage. However, things take a devastating turn when they disappear during a flood.

title: Black & White
subTitle: A suicide bomber comes to India with a deadly mission. However, his mind changes after spending time with a professor.

title: Saina
subTitle: Professional badminton player Saina Nehwal wins more than 24 international titles and achieves the top world spot in 2015.

title: Mrs. Chatterjee vs Norway
subTitle: Debika Chatterjee, an Indian woman living in Norway with her family, fights to regain custody of her children after Norwegian authorities take them away from her.

title: Chhatriwali
subTitle: While struggling to find work, Sanya accepts a unique job and ends up leading a quiet revolution in how her community thinks about health and responsibility.

title: Yudhra
subTitle: A vengeful youth infiltrates a dangerous cartel to avenge the death of his parents. As he delves deeper, he uncovers shocking truths about his past that challenge his resolve and moral boundaries.

title: Mukkabaaz
subTitle: Shravan Singh, an aspiring boxer, finds an enemy in Bhagwan Das Mishra, the head of a boxing federation. Thereafter, things take a turn for the worse after he falls for Bhagwan's niece, Sunaina.
